{"questionId":"2603622","questionHtml":"<p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>10</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn></msqrt></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>×</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>one correct magnitude <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct substitution of their magnitudes and scalar product&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>×</mo><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>×</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>×</mo><msqrt><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></mfrac></math> (or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>10</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2603622","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ1.12a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that 4t=10t2+12t+18.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.13—Scalar (dot) product","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}